race.comment: MOEGREEN (2) has a nice association with jockey Cormack who has only missed a drum once in nine steers and has hit a purple patch of form of late. Should be right there when the whips are cracking. COLOURS OF AUTUMN (7) has won three of six over this seven-furlong journey and will be at peak fitness for this fourth-up from the spell. Cannot be discounted lightly. BURRANEER BUOY (4) has won three of his past four outings with Fry being in the saddle for two of those victories. Hard to knock winning form. TURN BIRD (1) has two wins and a second from three attempts over this track and trip and should get a gun run in transit from the inside alley. Plenty to like about his prospects. BRAVE AGENDA (8) best of the rest from the low draw.
